To solve this, we first need to understand that each exterior angle of a regular pentagon (and hence, each angle formed by extending the sides of the same regular pentagon) is the supplement of each interior angle of the octagon formed by the intersection of these extended lines. The measure of each interior angle of a regular pentagon is $\frac{(5-2)(180^\circ)}{5}=108^\circ$. Hence each exterior angle is $180^\circ-108^\circ=72^\circ$.</think>

